Actually I have tried onnxruntime v1.0 and v1.1,  both of them get the same link error.  is my TensorRT problem?  
need to install low version tensorRT ?

we don't have jetson xavier available for us to test locally.
recently someone else successfully built on xavier. see https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3307

from your error above, it looks like there's missing references to NvMedia* functions.
I believe that comes from libnvmedia.so which I think is only available on Xavier. Since we primarily tested on Jetson Nano, that wasn't available. 

also I noticed you have gencode=arch=compute_75,code=sm_75") # Jetson support
I think Xavier is actually compute_72 , sm_72 
btw, we have only tested with gencode=arch=compute_53,code=sm_53 # 
since we've only tested on Jetson Nano. 
can you try compute_53, sm_53 ?

thanks for reply. change to 53 has the same problem.  when I install Target Components using SDK Manager4.3, Mutimedia component failed. is this reason ?

linking to other thread in case others encounter this issue.
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3307#issuecomment-606552992

close it.  [https://forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/tensorrt-can-not-work-with-libnvinfer-so/117928](url)

> Please noticed that there are some strong dependencies between OS(GPU driver) and libraries.

So it is required to use the OS and package from the same JetPack version to avoid incompatibility.

@jywu-msft 
tensorRT did not setup DLA engine ? 
your verbose.log shows
2020-02-26 18:13:28.123485238 [V:onnxruntime:, inference_session.cc:642 TransformGraph] All nodes have been placed on [TensorrtExecutionProvider].
That means all nodes are executing on GPU via TensorRT
[refer to](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3024#issuecomment-591771211)

> @jywu-msft
> tensorRT did not setup DLA engine ?
> your verbose.log shows
> 2020-02-26 18:13:28.123485238 [V:onnxruntime:, inference_session.cc:642 TransformGraph] All nodes have been placed on [TensorrtExecutionProvider].
> That means all nodes are executing on GPU via TensorRT
> [refer to](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/3024#issuecomment-591771211)

onnxruntime's TensorRT integration doesn't support DLA cores. Jetson Xavier wasn't a target for us to support. That could change in the future.
